I came into this location for a half dozen of donuts. They weren't for me, so I was texting with who they were for to coordinate with what they wanted with what was available. An older man with a heavy accent gestured for me to come forward. I informed him I would be up shortly. After a few minutes, while I'm waiting for a response, still very obviously looking specifically at the donuts, he tells me to come forward again. I told him I was still deciding, and due to his accent I genuinely couldn't understand what he was saying, but it was along the lines of 'come up to order or sit down'..... I'm trying to decide what to purchase! If I'm sitting, I can't see. If I come to the counter, I'm in someone's way. I was out of the way in a spot where I could see the items I wanted to see. Then he says 'I'm telling you...*indistinguishable*" while ROLLING his eyes at me. There's no reason to speak to a customer this way. I just turned around and walked out. I worked food service for over 5 years, I've never had such a rude customer. If I needed to stand in a different spot, I would have if asked in a fair and clear manner. Having an accent is never an issue, but it is when you don't speak UP and help me understand what you're saying. Otherwise you lose business, like today. I will not return here.
